<P>And then, sure they that are already come to <HI>Old Age,</HI> had need make sure of <HI>Conversion,</HI> before it become altogether too late, hopeless, helpless, &amp; unattainable. My Fathers, you are now got into the <HI>winter</HI> of your Lives; Old Age begins to S<HI>now</HI> upon your heads; &amp; your whole face, is that of the earth in <HI>winter.</HI> The Jews generally inter'd their <HI>Dead</HI> un|der an <HI>Oak:</HI> see 1 Sam. 21. 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">.] pleased perhaps with some such parallel as this; that as the <HI>Tree</HI> seeming|ly <HI>dead</HI> in the <HI>winter,</HI> had every Spring an Annual
